# Logs - not needed
*.log
GameEngineLog.txt
imgui.ini

# Visual Studio IDE cache (regenerates automatically - not your real project
# settings; those live in .sln/.vcxproj/.vcxproj.user, which stay tracked).
.vs/

# Compiler intermediate/output junk - scoped to the actual build folders ONLY,
# at any depth (the "**/" prefix is required, otherwise these only match at
# the repo root and miss ComponentFramework/Debug, ComponentFramework/x64, etc).
# This deliberately does NOT use a global "*.obj" rule, because
# meshes/*.obj are real Blender model assets and must never be touched here.
#
# .exe IS ignored here: it's your own compiled output, changes on every
# build, and is trivially regenerated - exactly the noise we want gone.
# .dll is the ONE exception left untouched everywhere: those are third-party
# runtime dependencies (SDL3/OpenGL) that you don't compile yourself, so if
# one is ever deliberately placed here it stays tracked/synced instead of
# silently disappearing (that's what caused the missing-DLL problem before).
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.obj
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.pdb
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.ilk
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.idb
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.tlog
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.lastbuildstate
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.recipe
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.iobj
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.ipdb
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.exe
**/[Dd]ebug/**/*.FileListAbsolute.txt

**/[Rr]elease/**/*.obj
**/[Rr]elease/**/*.pdb
**/[Rr]elease/**/*.ilk
**/[Rr]elease/**/*.idb
**/[Rr]elease/**/*.tlog
**/[Rr]elease/**/*.lastbuildstate
**/[Rr]elease/**/*.recipe
**/[Rr]elease/**/*.iobj
**/[Rr]elease/**/*.ipdb
**/[Rr]elease/**/*.exe
**/[Rr]elease/**/*.FileListAbsolute.txt

**/x64/**/*.obj
**/x64/**/*.pdb
**/x64/**/*.ilk
**/x64/**/*.idb
**/x64/**/*.tlog
**/x64/**/*.lastbuildstate
**/x64/**/*.recipe
**/x64/**/*.iobj
**/x64/**/*.ipdb
**/x64/**/*.exe
**/x64/**/*.FileListAbsolute.txt

**/x86/**/*.obj
**/x86/**/*.pdb
**/x86/**/*.ilk
**/x86/**/*.idb
**/x86/**/*.tlog
**/x86/**/*.lastbuildstate
**/x86/**/*.recipe
**/x86/**/*.iobj
**/x86/**/*.ipdb
**/x86/**/*.exe
**/x86/**/*.FileListAbsolute.txt

